				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok everyone.  I know the bolt spell may &quot;suck&quot; to you mages that can't solo, or just plain don't.  Whatever and I don't care which.  But the secret I have found is that when you are soloing (which I do alot of) then your bolt spell is great.  Who cares if it doesn't do the full damage every single time.  Thats why you RECAST it as soon as you can.  Also let your pet tank and don't stand so far away from the melee to cast it.  I have not had a problem with it since i was 20.  Now 24 and I just use both spells depending on what I am doing.  If you in group then use the Spike series.  Soloing use the bolt series.  Just my thought.  I have 2 mages on different servers, 24 mage on Innoruk and 38 on Xegony (who just retired).   Well use this to either give you ideas or piss ya off.  Makes no matter to me )  Just experiment to find out what works for you. Just stop all the bellyaching cause your spell only hit for 20 points instead of 154 points.  Think of D&amp;D game with THAC0 and just imagine you got a bad roll of the dice.  8P  Peachy day all<BR>
<BR>
Belegereth<BR>
24th season mage 
