			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hi all! This is the first complete list Ive read. I read every single article on this spell. Just because it has the most info on one of the most troublesome dilemnas of mages. WHAT DO YOU SPEC IN? I myself found that my shock line was actually resisted quite a bit. When you get to higher lvs, and your in guk, or sebilis, and your fighting some casters, they have some resistance to a bit of everything, but shock is usually resisted, but my fire ones, are not, they do about half the dmg they should, but they do dmg. But most of the time if one doesnt work, I try my other memed spells. But one thing i think most of you forgot to mention, is that YOU DONT SUFFER! IF you choose evoc, to spec in, then you get a BONUS to evoc, less mana, and less casting time. And the same for conj, I think most of you are taking spec for granted. If you pick one over the other, it doesnt mean you suffer a penalty, you are rewarded for a bonus. But as well, remember, you can still spec in all specs, but just only one can go over 50. As far as which to spec in...hmm. It depends on your race, and stats mostly. If your a human, i would spec in conj, since it costs more mana, but for erudite, evoc. But also, consider what strategies you use to win the battle. If you always take on red cons or higher yellow cons, then most likely your pet dies more often, so in battle, if you need to resummon a pet, conjuration is the way to go, BY FAR!! I personally dont use that tactic, im fine with my nuke method, I just nuke the thing till it gets to half hp, by the time its down to half hp, my pet still has 90% health, so I just do one more dd spell, then back off and let my pet do the rest, but also, if I cast it so many times in row, the thing comes after me, so i just run around, and my pet attacks it, sort of reverse kitting, but someone has to play the bait, I usually always have sow when taking on red or yellow cons, but thats just because someone who can sow is near. I have never died from a yellow con when i had half mana, and my pet had full health. As I said, you must pick which to spec in based on your tactics, I personally like to summon one pet per zone. hehe, well, I hope this helps! BTW, MAGES RULE!!!! Ive never dueled a warrior who has bested my mage, or for that matter, ive never been defeated in a duel, hehe, I duel about twice per new spell lv, hehe. BYE ALL!! <BR>
<BR>
Ravenclaw Shadowalker<BR>
Dark Elf Elementist<BR>
Xev server<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

